            <abstract>
                <p>The universal chronicle of <persName ref="PRS4711Giyorgis"/> was translated to Gǝʿǝz and augmented with accounts concerning the history of Ethiopia, 
                    possibly at the time of <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY"/>, see <bibl><ptr target="bm:Kropp2016Zekra"/><citedRange unit="page">5</citedRange></bibl>.
                An abbreviation of this lenghty work was included in the column reserved to <foreign xml:lang="gez">tārik</foreign> in calendaric tables. These entries were in their turn 
                    again converted into an abbreviated text, <ref type="work" corresp="LIT4089Introduction"/>, which forms the introduction of a type of <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2352ShortC"/>.
                    Other excerpts of the History are included as an introduction, <ref type="work" corresp="LIT4724WaldaAmidIntroduction"/>, in other historiographic works, such as the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT4090Haylu"/>.</p>
            </abstract>
